{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"492ecc32-2059-4d79-9a08-e2d496181717","content":"No existing files found — this is a guidance request. Here's how to convert your page:\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"48\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **only structural change** is adding `xmlns:vm` and `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` at the page level. All existing `{Binding …}` expressions automatically become compiled bindings.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nCompiled bindings are validated by the XAML compiler (`XamlC`). To ensure errors surface as **build errors**:\n\n**a) Confirm XamlC is enabled** (on by default in .NET MAUI, but you can be explicit in your `.csproj`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <XamlCompilation>Compile</XamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**b) Treat warnings as errors** for even stricter enforcement:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <WarningsAsErrors>XC0045;XC0022</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nNow if you typo a property name (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`), the build **fails** instead of silently returning `null` at runtime.\n\n### Key rules to remember\n\n| Do | Don't |\n|---|---|\n| Set `x:DataType` on the root or any container element | Use `{Binding Path=…}` against an untyped context |\n| Use `x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\"` to **opt out** for a specific subtree (e.g., a `DataTemplate` bound at runtime) | Mix compiled and non-compiled bindings in the same scope without explicitly nulling the type |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"71993341-5c0e-43ae-8efb-969e5f8d3213","outputTokens":708,"requestId":"3C24:1E2E16:D3F13C:107B195:6A0128F4"},"id":"9a26897d-eded-48b8-b4f2-dfd31389b849","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:55:30.516Z","parentId":"e026da6d-374b-435e-b97f-671eb0b6de69"}
